Please be aware this spec file is based on the original spec file that nginx provides in their source rpm packages.

You can build the rpms by running the build script: ./build-ulyaoth-nginx-stable-and-mainline-modules.sh headers-more

The below command would build both the stable and mainline module.

So you can build a module rpm as following:
wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ulyaoth/repository/master/ulyaoth-nginx-modules/build-ulyaoth-nginx-stable-and-mainline-modules.sh ; chmod +x build-ulyaoth-nginx-stable-and-mainline-modules.sh ; ./build-ulyaoth-nginx-stable-and-mainline-modules.sh headers-more

Supported modules:
headers-more (https://github.com/openresty/headers-more-nginx-module)
echo (https://github.com/openresty/echo-nginx-module)
pam (https://github.com/stogh/ngx_http_auth_pam_module)
form-input (https://github.com/calio/form-input-nginx-module)
devel-kit (https://github.com/simpl/ngx_devel_kit)
encrypted-session (https://github.com/openresty/encrypted-session-nginx-module)
array-var (https://github.com/openresty/array-var-nginx-module)
naxsi (https://github.com/nbs-system/naxsi)